34void testBitAndSExt32(int32_t value, int64_t mask)
35{
36 Procedure proc;
37 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
38 root->appendNewControlValue(
39 proc, Return, Origin(),
40 root->appendNew<Value>(
41 proc, BitAnd, Origin(),
42 root->appendNew<Value>(
43 proc, SExt32, Origin(),
44 root->appendNew<Value>(
45 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
46 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0))),
47 root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), mask)));
48
49 CHECK(compileAndRun<int64_t>(proc, value) == (static_cast<int64_t>(value) & mask));
50}

52void testBasicSelect()
53{
54 Procedure proc;
55 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
56 root->appendNewControlValue(
57 proc, Return, Origin(),
58 root->appendNew<Value>(
59 proc, Select, Origin(),
60 root->appendNew<Value>(
61 proc, Equal, Origin(),
62 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0),
63 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 42)),
64 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1),
65 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2)));
66
67 auto code = compileProc(proc);
68 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 42, 1, 2) == 1);
69 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 42, 642462, 32533) == 642462);
70 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 43, 1, 2) == 2);
71 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 43, 642462, 32533) == 32533);
72}

93void testSelectCompareDouble()
94{
95 Procedure proc;
96 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
97 root->appendNewControlValue(
98 proc, Return, Origin(),
99 root->appendNew<Value>(
100 proc, Select, Origin(),
101 root->appendNew<Value>(
102 proc, LessThan, Origin(),
103 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0),
104 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1)),
105 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0),
106 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1)));
107
108 auto code = compileProc(proc);
109 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, -1.0, 1.0, 1, 2) == 1);
110 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 42.5, 42.51, 642462, 32533) == 642462);
111 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, PNaN, 0.0, 1, 2) == 2);
112 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 42.51, 42.5, 642462, 32533) == 32533);
113 CHECK(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 42.52, 42.52, 524978245, 352) == 352);
114}

116template<B3::Opcode opcode>
117void testSelectCompareFloat(float a, float b, bool (*operation)(float, float))
118{
119 Procedure proc;
120 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
121 Value* argument1int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
122 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
123 Value* argument2int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
124 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
125 Value* floatValue1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument1int32);
126 Value* floatValue2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument2int32);
127
128 root->appendNewControlValue(
129 proc, Return, Origin(),
130 root->appendNew<Value>(
131 proc, Select, Origin(),
132 root->appendNew<Value>(
133 proc, opcode, Origin(),
134 floatValue1,
135 floatValue2),
136 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2),
137 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR3)));
138 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(b), 42, -5), operation(a, b) ? 42 : -5));
139}
140
141void testSelectCompareFloat(float a, float b)
142{
143 testSelectCompareFloat<Equal>(a, b, [](float a, float b) -> bool { return a == b; });
144 testSelectCompareFloat<NotEqual>(a, b, [](float a, float b) -> bool { return a != b; });
145 testSelectCompareFloat<LessThan>(a, b, [](float a, float b) -> bool { return a < b; });
146 testSelectCompareFloat<GreaterThan>(a, b, [](float a, float b) -> bool { return a > b; });
147 testSelectCompareFloat<LessEqual>(a, b, [](float a, float b) -> bool { return a <= b; });
148 testSelectCompareFloat<GreaterEqual>(a, b, [](float a, float b) -> bool { return a >= b; });
149 testSelectCompareFloat<EqualOrUnordered>(a, b, [](float a, float b) -> bool { return a != a || b != b || a == b; });
150}

190void testSelectDouble()
191{
192 Procedure proc;
193 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
194 root->appendNewControlValue(
195 proc, Return, Origin(),
196 root->appendNew<Value>(
197 proc, Select, Origin(),
198 root->appendNew<Value>(
199 proc, Equal, Origin(),
200 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0),
201 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 42)),
202 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0),
203 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1)));
204
205 auto code = compileProc(proc);
206 CHECK(invoke<double>(*code, 42, 1.5, 2.6) == 1.5);
207 CHECK(invoke<double>(*code, 42, 642462.7, 32533.8) == 642462.7);
208 CHECK(invoke<double>(*code, 43, 1.9, 2.0) == 2.0);
209 CHECK(invoke<double>(*code, 43, 642462.1, 32533.2) == 32533.2);
210}

254void testSelectDoubleCompareFloat(float a, float b)
255{
256 Procedure proc;
257 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
258 Value* argument1int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
259 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
260 Value* argument2int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
261 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
262 Value* floatValue1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument1int32);
263 Value* floatValue2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument2int32);
264
265 root->appendNewControlValue(
266 proc, Return, Origin(),
267 root->appendNew<Value>(
268 proc, Select, Origin(),
269 root->appendNew<Value>(
270 proc, LessThan, Origin(),
271 floatValue1,
272 floatValue2),
273 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0),
274 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1)));
275
276 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<double>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(b), 42.1, -M_PI), a < b ? 42.1 : -M_PI));
277}

279void testSelectFloatCompareFloat(float a, float b)
280{
281 Procedure proc;
282 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
283 Value* argument1int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
284 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
285 Value* argument2int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
286 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
287 Value* argument3int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
288 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2));
289 Value* argument4int32 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
290 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR3));
291 Value* floatValue1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument1int32);
292 Value* floatValue2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument2int32);
293 Value* floatValue3 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument3int32);
294 Value* floatValue4 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(), argument4int32);
295
296 root->appendNewControlValue(
297 proc, Return, Origin(),
298 root->appendNew<Value>(
299 proc, Select, Origin(),
300 root->appendNew<Value>(
301 proc, LessThan, Origin(),
302 floatValue1,
303 floatValue2),
304 floatValue3,
305 floatValue4));
306
307 CHECK(isIdentical(compileAndRun<float>(proc, bitwise_cast<int32_t>(a), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(b), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(1.1f), bitwise_cast<int32_t>(-42.f)), a < b ? 1.1f : -42.f));

311template<B3::Opcode opcode>
312void testSelectDoubleCompareDouble(bool (*operation)(double, double))
313{
314 { // Compare arguments and selected arguments are all different.
315 Procedure proc;
316 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
317 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
318 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1);
319 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR2);
320 Value* arg3 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR3);
321
322 root->appendNewControlValue(
323 proc, Return, Origin(),
324 root->appendNew<Value>(
325 proc, Select, Origin(),
326 root->appendNew<Value>(
327 proc, opcode, Origin(),
328 arg0,
329 arg1),
330 arg2,
331 arg3));
332 auto code = compileProc(proc);
333
334 for (auto& left : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
335 for (auto& right : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
336 double expected = operation(left.value, right.value) ? 42.5 : -66.5;
337 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, left.value, right.value, 42.5, -66.5), expected));
338 }
339 }
340 }
341 { // Compare arguments and selected arguments are all different. "thenCase" is live after operation.
342 Procedure proc;
343 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
344 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
345 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1);
346 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR2);
347 Value* arg3 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR3);
348
349 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Select, Origin(),
350 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, opcode, Origin(), arg0, arg1),
351 arg2,
352 arg3);
353
354 PatchpointValue* keepValuesLive = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
355 keepValuesLive->append(ConstrainedValue(arg2, ValueRep::SomeRegister));
356 keepValuesLive->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
357
358 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
359 auto code = compileProc(proc);
360
361 for (auto& left : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
362 for (auto& right : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
363 double expected = operation(left.value, right.value) ? 42.5 : -66.5;
364 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, left.value, right.value, 42.5, -66.5), expected));
365 }
366 }
367 }
368 { // Compare arguments and selected arguments are all different. "elseCase" is live after operation.
369 Procedure proc;
370 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
371 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
372 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1);
373 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR2);
374 Value* arg3 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR3);
375
376 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Select, Origin(),
377 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, opcode, Origin(), arg0, arg1),
378 arg2,
379 arg3);
380
381 PatchpointValue* keepValuesLive = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
382 keepValuesLive->append(ConstrainedValue(arg3, ValueRep::SomeRegister));
383 keepValuesLive->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
384
385 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
386 auto code = compileProc(proc);
387
388 for (auto& left : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
389 for (auto& right : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
390 double expected = operation(left.value, right.value) ? 42.5 : -66.5;
391 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, left.value, right.value, 42.5, -66.5), expected));
392 }
393 }
394 }
395 { // Compare arguments and selected arguments are all different. Both cases are live after operation.
396 Procedure proc;
397 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
398 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
399 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1);
400 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR2);
401 Value* arg3 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR3);
402
403 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Select, Origin(),
404 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, opcode, Origin(), arg0, arg1),
405 arg2,
406 arg3);
407
408 PatchpointValue* keepValuesLive = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
409 keepValuesLive->append(ConstrainedValue(arg2, ValueRep::SomeRegister));
410 keepValuesLive->append(ConstrainedValue(arg3, ValueRep::SomeRegister));
411 keepValuesLive->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
412
413 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
414 auto code = compileProc(proc);
415
416 for (auto& left : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
417 for (auto& right : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
418 double expected = operation(left.value, right.value) ? 42.5 : -66.5;
419 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, left.value, right.value, 42.5, -66.5), expected));
420 }
421 }
422 }
423 { // The left argument is the same as the "elseCase" argument.
424 Procedure proc;
425 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
426 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
427 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1);
428 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR2);
429
430 root->appendNewControlValue(
431 proc, Return, Origin(),
432 root->appendNew<Value>(
433 proc, Select, Origin(),
434 root->appendNew<Value>(
435 proc, opcode, Origin(),
436 arg0,
437 arg1),
438 arg2,
439 arg0));
440 auto code = compileProc(proc);
441
442 for (auto& left : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
443 for (auto& right : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
444 double expected = operation(left.value, right.value) ? 42.5 : left.value;
445 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, left.value, right.value, 42.5, left.value), expected));
446 }
447 }
448 }
449 { // The left argument is the same as the "elseCase" argument. "thenCase" is live after operation.
450 Procedure proc;
451 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
452 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
453 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR1);
454 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR2);
455
456 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Select, Origin(),
457 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, opcode, Origin(), arg0, arg1),
458 arg2,
459 arg0);
460
461 PatchpointValue* keepValuesLive = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
462 keepValuesLive->append(ConstrainedValue(arg2, ValueRep::SomeRegister));
463 keepValuesLive->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
464
465 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
466 auto code = compileProc(proc);
467
468 for (auto& left : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
469 for (auto& right : floatingPointOperands<double>()) {
470 double expected = operation(left.value, right.value) ? 42.5 : left.value;
471 CHECK(isIdentical(invoke<double>(*code, left.value, right.value, 42.5, left.value), expected));
472 }
473 }
474 }
475}

488template<B3::Opcode opcode>
489void testSelectFloatCompareFloat(bool (*operation)(float, float))
490{
491 { // Compare arguments and selected arguments are all different.
492 Procedure proc;
493 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
494
495 Value* arg0 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(),
496 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
497 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)));
498 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(),
499 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
500 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1)));
501 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(),
502 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
503 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2)));
504 Value* arg3 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitwiseCast, Origin(),
505 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(),
506 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR3)));
507
508 root->appendNewControlValue(
509 proc, Return, Origin(),
510 root->appendNew<Value>(
511 proc, Select, Origin(),
512 root->appendNew<Value>(
513 proc, opcode, Origin(),
514 arg0,
515 arg1),
516 arg2,
517 arg3));
518 auto code = compileProc(proc);
519
520 for (auto& left : floatingPointOperands<float>()) {
521 for (auto& right : floatingPointOperands<float>()) {

699void testSelectFloatCompareFloatWithAliasing()
700{
701 testSelectFloatCompareFloat<Equal>([](float a, float b) -> bool { return a == b; });
702 testSelectFloatCompareFloat<NotEqual>([](float a, float b) -> bool { return a != b; });
703 testSelectFloatCompareFloat<LessThan>([](float a, float b) -> bool { return a < b; });
704 testSelectFloatCompareFloat<GreaterThan>([](float a, float b) -> bool { return a > b; });
705 testSelectFloatCompareFloat<LessEqual>([](float a, float b) -> bool { return a <= b; });
706 testSelectFloatCompareFloat<GreaterEqual>([](float a, float b) -> bool { return a >= b; });
707 testSelectFloatCompareFloat<EqualOrUnordered>([](float a, float b) -> bool { return a != a || b != b || a == b; });
708}

755void testCheckSelect()
756{
757 Procedure proc;
758 if (proc.optLevel() < 1)
759 return;
760 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
761
762 CheckValue* check = root->appendNew<CheckValue>(
763 proc, Check, Origin(),
764 root->appendNew<Value>(
765 proc, Add, Origin(),
766 root->appendNew<Value>(
767 proc, Select, Origin(),
768 root->appendNew<Value>(
769 proc, BitAnd, Origin(),
770 root->appendNew<Value>(

772 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(
773 proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)),

775 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), -42),
776 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 35)),
777 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 42)));

785 jit.emitFunctionEpilogue();

796 CHECK(invoke<int>(*code, false) == 666);
797}

919
920double b3Pow(double x, int y)
921{
922 if (y < 0 || y > 1000)
923 return pow(x, y);
924 double result = 1;
925 while (y) {
926 if (y & 1)
927 result *= x;
928 x *= x;
929 y >>= 1;
930 }
931 return result;
932}

935{

1023void testBranch64Equal(int64_t left, int64_t right)
1024{
1025 Procedure proc;
1026 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1027 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
1028 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
1029
1030 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1031 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
1032 root->appendNewControlValue(
1033 proc, Branch, Origin(),
1034 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(), arg1, arg2),
1035 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
1036
1037 bool trueResult = true;
1038 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(
1039 proc, Return, Origin(),
1040 thenCase->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1041 proc, Load8Z, Origin(),
1042 thenCase->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &trueResult)));
1043
1044 bool elseResult = false;
1045 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(
1046 proc, Return, Origin(),
1047 elseCase->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1048 proc, Load8Z, Origin(),
1049 elseCase->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &elseResult)));
1050
1051 CHECK(compileAndRun<bool>(proc, left, right) == (left == right));
1052}

1103 proc, Return, Origin(),

1441void testSpillDefSmallerThanUse()
1442{
1443 Procedure proc;
1444 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1445
1446 // Move32.
1447 Value* arg32 = root->appendNew<Value>(
1448 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1449 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
1450 Value* arg64 = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZExt32, Origin(), arg32);
1451
1452 // Make sure arg64 is on the stack.
1453 PatchpointValue* forceSpill = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int64, Origin());
1454 RegisterSet clobberSet = RegisterSet::allGPRs();
1455 clobberSet.exclude(RegisterSet::stackRegisters());
1456 clobberSet.exclude(RegisterSet::reservedHardwareRegisters());
1457 clobberSet.clear(GPRInfo::returnValueGPR); // Force the return value for aliasing below.
1458 forceSpill->clobberLate(clobberSet);
1459 forceSpill->setGenerator(
1460 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1461 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1462 jit.xor64(params[0].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1463 });
1464
1465 // On x86, Sub admit an address for any operand. If it uses the stack, the top bits must be zero.
1466 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Sub, Origin(), forceSpill, arg64);
1467 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
1468
1469 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1470 CHECK(invoke<int64_t>(*code, 0xffffffff00000000) == 0);
1471}
1472
1473void testSpillUseLargerThanDef()
1474{
1475 Procedure proc;
1476 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1477 BasicBlock* thenCase = proc.addBlock();
1478 BasicBlock* elseCase = proc.addBlock();
1479 BasicBlock* tail = proc.addBlock();
1480
1481 RegisterSet clobberSet = RegisterSet::allGPRs();
1482 clobberSet.exclude(RegisterSet::stackRegisters());
1483 clobberSet.exclude(RegisterSet::reservedHardwareRegisters());
1484
1485 Value* condition = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1486 Value* argument = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
1487 root->appendNewControlValue(
1488 proc, Branch, Origin(),
1489 root->appendNew<Value>(
1490 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
1491 condition),
1492 FrequentedBlock(thenCase), FrequentedBlock(elseCase));
1493
1494 Value* truncated = thenCase->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZExt32, Origin(),
1495 thenCase->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), argument));
1496 UpsilonValue* thenResult = thenCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), truncated);
1497 thenCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
1498
1499 UpsilonValue* elseResult = elseCase->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), argument);
1500 elseCase->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(tail));
1501
1502 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {
1503 PatchpointValue* preventTailDuplication = tail->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
1504 preventTailDuplication->clobberLate(clobberSet);
1505 preventTailDuplication->setGenerator([] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
1506 }
1507
1508 PatchpointValue* forceSpill = tail->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
1509 forceSpill->clobberLate(clobberSet);
1510 forceSpill->setGenerator(
1511 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1512 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1513 clobberSet.forEach([&] (Reg reg) {
1514 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm64(0xffffffffffffffff), reg.gpr());
1515 });
1516 });
1517
1518 Value* phi = tail->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Int64, Origin());
1519 thenResult->setPhi(phi);
1520 elseResult->setPhi(phi);
1521 tail->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), phi);
1522
1523 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1524 CHECK(invoke<uint64_t>(*code, 1, 0xffffffff00000000) == 0);
1525 CHECK(invoke<uint64_t>(*code, 0, 0xffffffff00000000) == 0xffffffff00000000);
1526
1527 // A second time since the previous run is still on the stack.
1528 CHECK(invoke<uint64_t>(*code, 1, 0xffffffff00000000) == 0);
1529
1530}
1531
1532void testLateRegister()
1533{
1534 Procedure proc;
1535
1536 if (!proc.optLevel()) {
1537 // FIXME: Make O0 handle such situations:
1538 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=194633
1539 return;
1540 }
1541
1542 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1543
1544 // This works by making all but 1 register be input to the first patchpoint as LateRegister.
1545 // The other 1 register is just a regular Register input. We assert our result is the regular
1546 // register input. There would be no other way for the register allocator to arrange things
1547 // because LateRegister interferes with the result.
1548 // Then, the second patchpoint takes the result of the first as an argument and asks for
1549 // it in a register that was a LateRegister. This is to incentivize the register allocator
1550 // to use that LateRegister as the result for the first patchpoint. But of course it can not do that.
1551 // So it must issue a mov after the first patchpoint from the first's result into the second's input.
1552
1553 RegisterSet regs = RegisterSet::allGPRs();
1554 regs.exclude(RegisterSet::stackRegisters());
1555 regs.exclude(RegisterSet::reservedHardwareRegisters());
1556 Vector<Value*> lateUseArgs;
1557 unsigned result = 0;
1558 for (GPRReg reg = CCallHelpers::firstRegister(); reg <= CCallHelpers::lastRegister(); reg = CCallHelpers::nextRegister(reg)) {
1559 if (!regs.get(reg))
1560 continue;
1561 result++;
1562 if (reg == GPRInfo::regT0)
1563 continue;
1564 Value* value = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), 1);
1565 lateUseArgs.append(value);
1566 }
1567 Value* regularUse = root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), 1);
1568 PatchpointValue* firstPatchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int64, Origin());
1569 {
1570 unsigned i = 0;
1571 for (GPRReg reg = CCallHelpers::firstRegister(); reg <= CCallHelpers::lastRegister(); reg = CCallHelpers::nextRegister(reg)) {
1572 if (!regs.get(reg))
1573 continue;
1574 if (reg == GPRInfo::regT0)
1575 continue;
1576 Value* value = lateUseArgs[i++];
1577 firstPatchpoint->append(value, ValueRep::lateReg(reg));
1578 }
1579 firstPatchpoint->append(regularUse, ValueRep::reg(GPRInfo::regT0));
1580 }
1581
1582 firstPatchpoint->setGenerator(
1583 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1584 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1585 CHECK(params[0].gpr() == GPRInfo::regT0);
1586 // Note that regT0 should also start off as 1, so we're implicitly starting our add with 1, which is also an argument.
1587 unsigned skipped = 0;
1588 for (unsigned i = 1; i < params.size(); i++) {
1589 if (params[i].gpr() == params[0].gpr()) {
1590 skipped = i;
1591 continue;
1592 }
1593 jit.add64(params[i].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1594 }
1595 CHECK(!!skipped);
1596 });
1597
1598 PatchpointValue* secondPatchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int64, Origin());
1599 secondPatchpoint->append(firstPatchpoint, ValueRep::reg(GPRInfo::regT1));
1600 secondPatchpoint->setGenerator(
1601 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1602 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1603 CHECK(params[1].gpr() == GPRInfo::regT1);
1604 jit.nop();
1605 jit.nop();
1606 jit.move(params[1].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1607 jit.nop();
1608 jit.nop();
1609 });
1610 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), secondPatchpoint);
1611
1612 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1613 CHECK(invoke<uint64_t>(*code) == result);
1614}
1615
1616JSC_DECLARE_JIT_OPERATION(interpreterPrint, void, (Vector<intptr_t>* stream, intptr_t value));
1617JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(interpreterPrint, void, (Vector<intptr_t>* stream, intptr_t value))
1618{
1619 stream->append(value);
1620}
1621
1622void testInterpreter()
1623{
1624 // This implements a silly interpreter to test building custom switch statements using
1625 // Patchpoint.
1626
1627 Procedure proc;
1628
1629 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1630 BasicBlock* dispatch = proc.addBlock();
1631 BasicBlock* addToDataPointer = proc.addBlock();
1632 BasicBlock* addToCodePointer = proc.addBlock();
1633 BasicBlock* addToCodePointerTaken = proc.addBlock();
1634 BasicBlock* addToCodePointerNotTaken = proc.addBlock();
1635 BasicBlock* addToData = proc.addBlock();
1636 BasicBlock* print = proc.addBlock();
1637 BasicBlock* stop = proc.addBlock();
1638
1639 Variable* dataPointer = proc.addVariable(pointerType());
1640 Variable* codePointer = proc.addVariable(pointerType());
1641
1642 root->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1643 proc, Set, Origin(), dataPointer,
1644 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
1645 root->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1646 proc, Set, Origin(), codePointer,
1647 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
1648 Value* context = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
1649 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(dispatch));
1650
1651 // NOTE: It's totally valid for this patchpoint to be tail-duplicated.
1652 Value* codePointerValue =
1653 dispatch->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), codePointer);
1654 Value* opcode = dispatch->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1655 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(), codePointerValue);
1656 PatchpointValue* polyJump = dispatch->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
1657 polyJump->effects = Effects();
1658 polyJump->effects.terminal = true;
1659 polyJump->appendSomeRegister(opcode);
1660 polyJump->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
1661 polyJump->numGPScratchRegisters = 2;
1662 dispatch->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(addToDataPointer));
1663 dispatch->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(addToCodePointer));
1664 dispatch->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(addToData));
1665 dispatch->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(print));
1666 dispatch->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(stop));
1667
1668 // Our "opcodes".
1669 static constexpr intptr_t AddDP = 0;
1670 static constexpr intptr_t AddCP = 1;
1671 static constexpr intptr_t Add = 2;
1672 static constexpr intptr_t Print = 3;
1673 static constexpr intptr_t Stop = 4;
1674
1675 polyJump->setGenerator(
1676 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1677 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1678 Vector<Box<CCallHelpers::Label>> labels = params.successorLabels();
1679
1680 MacroAssemblerCodePtr<JITCompilationPtrTag>* jumpTable = bitwise_cast<MacroAssemblerCodePtr<JITCompilationPtrTag>*>(
1681 params.proc().addDataSection(sizeof(MacroAssemblerCodePtr<JITCompilationPtrTag>) * labels.size()));
1682
1683 GPRReg scratch = params.gpScratch(0);
1684
1685 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImmPtr(jumpTable), scratch);
1686 jit.load64(CCallHelpers::BaseIndex(scratch, params[0].gpr(), CCallHelpers::ScalePtr), scratch);
1687 jit.farJump(scratch, JITCompilationPtrTag);
1688
1689 jit.addLinkTask(
1690 [&, jumpTable, labels] (LinkBuffer& linkBuffer) {
1691 for (unsigned i = labels.size(); i--;)
1692 jumpTable[i] = linkBuffer.locationOf<JITCompilationPtrTag>(*labels[i]);
1693 });
1694 });
1695
1696 // AddDP <operand>: adds <operand> to DP.
1697 codePointerValue =
1698 addToDataPointer->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), codePointer);
1699 addToDataPointer->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1700 proc, Set, Origin(), dataPointer,
1701 addToDataPointer->appendNew<Value>(
1702 proc, B3::Add, Origin(),
1703 addToDataPointer->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), dataPointer),
1704 addToDataPointer->appendNew<Value>(
1705 proc, Mul, Origin(),
1706 addToDataPointer->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1707 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(), codePointerValue, static_cast<int32_t>(sizeof(intptr_t))),
1708 addToDataPointer->appendIntConstant(
1709 proc, Origin(), pointerType(), sizeof(intptr_t)))));
1710 addToDataPointer->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1711 proc, Set, Origin(), codePointer,
1712 addToDataPointer->appendNew<Value>(
1713 proc, B3::Add, Origin(), codePointerValue,
1714 addToDataPointer->appendIntConstant(
1715 proc, Origin(), pointerType(), sizeof(intptr_t) * 2)));
1716 addToDataPointer->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(dispatch));
1717
1718 // AddCP <operand>: adds <operand> to CP if the current value at DP is non-zero, otherwise
1719 // falls through normally.
1720 codePointerValue =
1721 addToCodePointer->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), codePointer);
1722 Value* dataPointerValue =
1723 addToCodePointer->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), dataPointer);
1724 addToCodePointer->appendNewControlValue(
1725 proc, Branch, Origin(),
1726 addToCodePointer->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1727 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(), dataPointerValue),
1728 FrequentedBlock(addToCodePointerTaken), FrequentedBlock(addToCodePointerNotTaken));
1729 addToCodePointerTaken->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1730 proc, Set, Origin(), codePointer,
1731 addToCodePointerTaken->appendNew<Value>(
1732 proc, B3::Add, Origin(), codePointerValue,
1733 addToCodePointerTaken->appendNew<Value>(
1734 proc, Mul, Origin(),
1735 addToCodePointerTaken->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1736 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(), codePointerValue, static_cast<int32_t>(sizeof(intptr_t))),
1737 addToCodePointerTaken->appendIntConstant(
1738 proc, Origin(), pointerType(), sizeof(intptr_t)))));
1739 addToCodePointerTaken->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(dispatch));
1740 addToCodePointerNotTaken->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1741 proc, Set, Origin(), codePointer,
1742 addToCodePointerNotTaken->appendNew<Value>(
1743 proc, B3::Add, Origin(), codePointerValue,
1744 addToCodePointerNotTaken->appendIntConstant(
1745 proc, Origin(), pointerType(), sizeof(intptr_t) * 2)));
1746 addToCodePointerNotTaken->appendNewControlValue(
1747 proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(dispatch));
1748
1749 // Add <operand>: adds <operand> to the slot pointed to by DP.
1750 codePointerValue = addToData->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), codePointer);
1751 dataPointerValue = addToData->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), dataPointer);
1752 addToData->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1753 proc, Store, Origin(),
1754 addToData->appendNew<Value>(
1755 proc, B3::Add, Origin(),
1756 addToData->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1757 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(), dataPointerValue),
1758 addToData->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1759 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(), codePointerValue, static_cast<int32_t>(sizeof(intptr_t)))),
1760 dataPointerValue);
1761 addToData->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1762 proc, Set, Origin(), codePointer,
1763 addToData->appendNew<Value>(
1764 proc, B3::Add, Origin(), codePointerValue,
1765 addToData->appendIntConstant(proc, Origin(), pointerType(), sizeof(intptr_t) * 2)));
1766 addToData->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(dispatch));
1767
1768 // Print: "prints" the value pointed to by DP. What this actually means is that the value is
1769 // appended to the stream vector by the interpreterPrint function.
1770 codePointerValue = print->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), codePointer);
1771 dataPointerValue = print->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), dataPointer);
1772 print->appendNew<CCallValue>(
1773 proc, Void, Origin(),
1774 print->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(
1775 proc, Origin(), tagCFunction<OperationPtrTag>(interpreterPrint)),
1776 context,
1777 print->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(), dataPointerValue));
1778 print->appendNew<VariableValue>(
1779 proc, Set, Origin(), codePointer,
1780 print->appendNew<Value>(
1781 proc, B3::Add, Origin(), codePointerValue,
1782 print->appendIntConstant(proc, Origin(), pointerType(), sizeof(intptr_t))));
1783 print->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), FrequentedBlock(dispatch));
1784
1785 // Stop: returns.
1786 stop->appendNewControlValue(
1787 proc, Return, Origin(),
1788 stop->appendIntConstant(proc, Origin(), pointerType(), 0));
1789
1790 auto interpreter = compileProc(proc);
1791
1792 Vector<uintptr_t> data;
1793 Vector<uintptr_t> code;
1794 Vector<uintptr_t> stream;
1795
1796 data.append(1);
1797 data.append(0);
1798
1799 if (shouldBeVerbose())
1800 dataLog("data = ", listDump(data), "\n");
1801
1802 // We'll write a program that prints the numbers 1..100.
1803 // We expect DP to point at #0.
1804 code.append(AddCP);
1805 code.append(6); // go to loop body
1806
1807 // Loop re-entry:
1808 // We expect DP to point at #1 and for #1 to be offset by -100.
1809 code.append(Add);
1810 code.append(100);
1811
1812 code.append(AddDP);
1813 code.append(-1);
1814
1815 // Loop header:
1816 // We expect DP to point at #0.
1817 code.append(AddDP);
1818 code.append(1);
1819
1820 code.append(Add);
1821 code.append(1);
1822
1823 code.append(Print);
1824
1825 code.append(Add);
1826 code.append(-100);
1827
1828 // We want to stop if it's zero and continue if it's non-zero. AddCP takes the branch if it's
1829 // non-zero.
1830 code.append(AddCP);
1831 code.append(-11); // go to loop re-entry.
1832
1833 code.append(Stop);
1834
1835 if (shouldBeVerbose())
1836 dataLog("code = ", listDump(code), "\n");
1837
1838 CHECK(!invoke<intptr_t>(*interpreter, data.data(), code.data(), &stream));
1839
1840 CHECK(stream.size() == 100);
1841 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 100; ++i)
1842 CHECK(stream[i] == i + 1);
1843
1844 if (shouldBeVerbose())
1845 dataLog("stream = ", listDump(stream), "\n");
1846}

2212void testEntrySwitchLoop()
2213{
2214 // This is a completely absurd use of EntrySwitch, where it impacts the loop condition. This
2215 // should cause duplication of either nearly the entire Procedure. At time of writing, we ended
2216 // up duplicating all of it, which is fine. It's important to test this case, to make sure that
2217 // the duplication algorithm can handle interesting control flow.
2218
2219 Procedure proc;
2220 proc.setNumEntrypoints(2);
2221
2222 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2223 BasicBlock* loopHeader = proc.addBlock();
2224 BasicBlock* loopFooter = proc.addBlock();
2225 BasicBlock* end = proc.addBlock();
2226
2227 UpsilonValue* initialValue = root->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(
2228 proc, Origin(), root->appendNew<Value>(
2229 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2230 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)));
2231 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Jump, Origin());
2232 root->setSuccessors(loopHeader);
2233
2234 Value* valueInLoop = loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Int32, Origin());
2235 initialValue->setPhi(valueInLoop);
2236 Value* newValue = loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(
2237 proc, Add, Origin(), valueInLoop,
2238 loopHeader->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 1));
2239 loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(proc, EntrySwitch, Origin());
2240 loopHeader->appendSuccessor(end);
2241 loopHeader->appendSuccessor(loopFooter);
2242
2243 loopFooter->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), newValue, valueInLoop);
2244 loopFooter->appendNew<Value>(
2245 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2246 loopFooter->appendNew<Value>(
2247 proc, LessThan, Origin(), newValue,
2248 loopFooter->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 100)));
2249 loopFooter->setSuccessors(loopHeader, end);
2250
2251 end->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), newValue);
2252
2253 prepareForGeneration(proc);
2254
2255 CCallHelpers jit;
2256 generate(proc, jit);
2257 LinkBuffer linkBuffer(jit, nullptr);
2258 CodeLocationLabel<JITCompilationPtrTag> labelOne = linkBuffer.locationOf<JITCompilationPtrTag>(proc.code().entrypointLabel(0));
2259 CodeLocationLabel<JITCompilationPtrTag> labelTwo = linkBuffer.locationOf<JITCompilationPtrTag>(proc.code().entrypointLabel(1));
2260
2261 MacroAssemblerCodeRef<JITCompilationPtrTag> codeRef = FINALIZE_CODE(linkBuffer, JITCompilationPtrTag, "testb3 compilation");
2262
2263 CHECK(invoke<int>(labelOne, 0) == 1);
2264 CHECK(invoke<int>(labelOne, 42) == 43);
2265 CHECK(invoke<int>(labelOne, 1000) == 1001);
2266
2267 CHECK(invoke<int>(labelTwo, 0) == 100);
2268 CHECK(invoke<int>(labelTwo, 42) == 100);
2269 CHECK(invoke<int>(labelTwo, 1000) == 1001);
2270}

2272void testSomeEarlyRegister()
2273{
2274 auto run = [&] (bool succeed) {
2275 Procedure proc;
2276
2277 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2278
2279 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int32, Origin());
2280 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::reg(GPRInfo::returnValueGPR) };
2281 bool ranFirstPatchpoint = false;
2282 patchpoint->setGenerator(
2283 [&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2284 CHECK(params[0].gpr() == GPRInfo::returnValueGPR);
2285 ranFirstPatchpoint = true;
2286 });
2287
2288 Value* arg = patchpoint;
2289
2290 patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int32, Origin());
2291 patchpoint->appendSomeRegister(arg);
2292 if (succeed)
2293 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::SomeEarlyRegister };
2294 bool ranSecondPatchpoint = false;
2295 unsigned optLevel = proc.optLevel();
2296 patchpoint->setGenerator(
2297 [&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2298 if (succeed)
2299 CHECK(params[0].gpr() != params[1].gpr());
2300 else if (optLevel > 1)
2301 CHECK(params[0].gpr() == params[1].gpr());
2302 ranSecondPatchpoint = true;
2303 });
2304
2305 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), patchpoint);
2306
2307 compileProc(proc);
2308 CHECK(ranFirstPatchpoint);
2309 CHECK(ranSecondPatchpoint);
2310 };
2311
2312 run(true);
2313 run(false);
2314}

2316void testBranchBitAndImmFusion(
2317 B3::Opcode valueModifier, Type valueType, int64_t constant,
2318 Air::Opcode expectedOpcode, Air::Arg::Kind firstKind)
2319{
2320 // Currently this test should pass on all CPUs. But some CPUs may not support this fused
2321 // instruction. It's OK to skip this test on those CPUs.
2322
2323 Procedure proc;
2324
2325 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2326 BasicBlock* one = proc.addBlock();
2327 BasicBlock* two = proc.addBlock();
2328
2329 Value* left = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2330
2331 if (valueModifier != Identity) {
2332 if (MemoryValue::accepts(valueModifier))
2333 left = root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, valueModifier, valueType, Origin(), left);
2334 else
2335 left = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, valueModifier, valueType, Origin(), left);
2336 }
2337
2338 root->appendNew<Value>(
2339 proc, Branch, Origin(),
2340 root->appendNew<Value>(
2341 proc, BitAnd, Origin(), left,
2342 root->appendIntConstant(proc, Origin(), valueType, constant)));
2343 root->setSuccessors(FrequentedBlock(one), FrequentedBlock(two));
2344
2345 one->appendNew<Value>(proc, Oops, Origin());
2346 two->appendNew<Value>(proc, Oops, Origin());
2347
2348 lowerToAirForTesting(proc);
2349
2350 // The first basic block must end in a BranchTest64(resCond, tmp, bitImm).
2351 Air::Inst terminal = proc.code()[0]->last();
2352 CHECK_EQ(terminal.kind.opcode, expectedOpcode);
2353 CHECK_EQ(terminal.args[0].kind(), Air::Arg::ResCond);
2354 CHECK_EQ(terminal.args[1].kind(), firstKind);
2355 CHECK(terminal.args[2].kind() == Air::Arg::BitImm || terminal.args[2].kind() == Air::Arg::BitImm64);
2356}

2358void testTerminalPatchpointThatNeedsToBeSpilled()
2359{
2360 // This is a unit test for how FTL's heap allocation fast paths behave.
2361 Procedure proc;
2362
2363 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2364 BasicBlock* success = proc.addBlock();
2365 BasicBlock* slowPath = proc.addBlock();
2366
2367 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int32, Origin());
2368 patchpoint->effects.terminal = true;
2369 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
2370
2371 root->appendSuccessor(success);
2372 root->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(slowPath, FrequencyClass::Rare));
2373
2374 patchpoint->setGenerator(
2375 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2376 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2377 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(42), params[0].gpr());
2378
2379 CCallHelpers::Jump jumpToSuccess;
2380 if (!params.fallsThroughToSuccessor(0))
2381 jumpToSuccess = jit.jump();
2382
2383 Vector<Box<CCallHelpers::Label>> labels = params.successorLabels();
2384
2385 params.addLatePath(
2386 [=] (CCallHelpers& jit) {
2387 if (jumpToSuccess.isSet())
2388 jumpToSuccess.linkTo(*labels[0], &jit);
2389 });
2390 });
2391
2392 Vector<Value*> args;
2393 {
2394 RegisterSet fillAllGPRsSet = proc.mutableGPRs();
2395 for (unsigned i = 0; i < fillAllGPRsSet.numberOfSetRegisters(); i++)
2396 args.append(success->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), i));
2397 }
2398
2399 {
2400 // Now force all values into every available register.
2401 PatchpointValue* p = success->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
2402 for (Value* v : args)
2403 p->append(v, ValueRep::SomeRegister);
2404 p->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
2405 }
2406
2407 {
2408 // Now require the original patchpoint to be materialized into a register.
2409 PatchpointValue* p = success->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
2410 p->append(patchpoint, ValueRep::SomeRegister);
2411 p->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
2412 }
2413
2414 success->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), success->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 10));
2415
2416 slowPath->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), slowPath->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 20));
2417
2418 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2419 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code), 10);
2420}

2422void testTerminalPatchpointThatNeedsToBeSpilled2()
2423{
2424 // This is a unit test for how FTL's heap allocation fast paths behave.
2425 Procedure proc;
2426
2427 // FIXME: Air O0/O1 allocator can't handle such programs. We rely on WasmAirIRGenerator
2428 // to not use any such constructs where the register allocator is cornered in such
2429 // a way.
2430 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=194633
2431 if (proc.optLevel() < 2)
2432 return;
2433
2434 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2435 BasicBlock* one = proc.addBlock();
2436 BasicBlock* success = proc.addBlock();
2437 BasicBlock* slowPath = proc.addBlock();
2438
2439 Value* arg = root->appendNew<Value>(
2440 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2441 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
2442
2443 root->appendNew<Value>(
2444 proc, Branch, Origin(), arg);
2445 root->appendSuccessor(one);
2446 root->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(slowPath, FrequencyClass::Rare));
2447
2448 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = one->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int32, Origin());
2449 patchpoint->effects.terminal = true;
2450 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
2451 patchpoint->append(arg, ValueRep::SomeRegister);
2452
2453 one->appendSuccessor(success);
2454 one->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(slowPath, FrequencyClass::Rare));
2455
2456 patchpoint->setGenerator(
2457 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2458 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2459 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(666), params[0].gpr());
2460 auto goToFastPath = jit.branch32(CCallHelpers::Equal, params[1].gpr(), CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(42));
2461 auto jumpToSlow = jit.jump();
2462
2463 // Make sure the asserts here pass.
2464 params.fallsThroughToSuccessor(0);
2465 params.fallsThroughToSuccessor(1);
2466
2467 Vector<Box<CCallHelpers::Label>> labels = params.successorLabels();
2468
2469 params.addLatePath(
2470 [=] (CCallHelpers& jit) {
2471 goToFastPath.linkTo(*labels[0], &jit);
2472 jumpToSlow.linkTo(*labels[1], &jit);
2473 });
2474 });
2475
2476 Vector<Value*> args;
2477 {
2478 RegisterSet fillAllGPRsSet = proc.mutableGPRs();
2479 for (unsigned i = 0; i < fillAllGPRsSet.numberOfSetRegisters(); i++)
2480 args.append(success->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), i));
2481 }
2482
2483 {
2484 // Now force all values into every available register.
2485 PatchpointValue* p = success->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
2486 for (Value* v : args)
2487 p->append(v, ValueRep::SomeRegister);
2488 p->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
2489 }
2490
2491 {
2492 // Now require the original patchpoint to be materialized into a register.
2493 PatchpointValue* p = success->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
2494 p->append(patchpoint, ValueRep::SomeRegister);
2495 p->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams&) { });
2496 }
2497
2498 success->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), patchpoint);
2499
2500 slowPath->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), arg);
2501
2502 auto original1 = Options::maxB3TailDupBlockSize();
2503 auto original2 = Options::maxB3TailDupBlockSuccessors();
2504
2505 // Tail duplication will break the critical edge we're trying to test because it
2506 // will clone the slowPath block for both edges to it!
2507 Options::maxB3TailDupBlockSize() = 0;
2508 Options::maxB3TailDupBlockSuccessors() = 0;
2509
2510 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2511 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 1), 1);
2512 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 0), 0);
2513 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 42), 666);
2514
2515 Options::maxB3TailDupBlockSize() = original1;
2516 Options::maxB3TailDupBlockSuccessors() = original2;
2517}

2519void testPatchpointTerminalReturnValue(bool successIsRare)
2520{
2521 // This is a unit test for how FTL's heap allocation fast paths behave.
2522 Procedure proc;
2523
2524 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2525 BasicBlock* success = proc.addBlock();
2526 BasicBlock* slowPath = proc.addBlock();
2527 BasicBlock* continuation = proc.addBlock();
2528
2529 Value* arg = root->appendNew<Value>(
2530 proc, Trunc, Origin(),
2531 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
2532
2533 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Int32, Origin());
2534 patchpoint->effects.terminal = true;
2535 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
2536
2537 if (successIsRare) {
2538 root->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(success, FrequencyClass::Rare));
2539 root->appendSuccessor(slowPath);
2540 } else {
2541 root->appendSuccessor(success);
2542 root->appendSuccessor(FrequentedBlock(slowPath, FrequencyClass::Rare));
2543 }
2544
2545 patchpoint->appendSomeRegister(arg);
2546
2547 patchpoint->setGenerator(
2548 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
2549 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
2550
2551 CCallHelpers::Jump jumpToSlow =
2552 jit.branch32(CCallHelpers::Above, params[1].gpr(), CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(42));
2553
2554 jit.add32(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(31), params[1].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
2555
2556 CCallHelpers::Jump jumpToSuccess;
2557 if (!params.fallsThroughToSuccessor(0))
2558 jumpToSuccess = jit.jump();
2559
2560 Vector<Box<CCallHelpers::Label>> labels = params.successorLabels();
2561
2562 params.addLatePath(
2563 [=] (CCallHelpers& jit) {
2564 jumpToSlow.linkTo(*labels[1], &jit);
2565 if (jumpToSuccess.isSet())
2566 jumpToSuccess.linkTo(*labels[0], &jit);
2567 });
2568 });
2569
2570 UpsilonValue* successUpsilon = success->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), patchpoint);
2571 success->appendNew<Value>(proc, Jump, Origin());
2572 success->setSuccessors(continuation);
2573
2574 UpsilonValue* slowPathUpsilon = slowPath->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(
2575 proc, Origin(), slowPath->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 666));
2576 slowPath->appendNew<Value>(proc, Jump, Origin());
2577 slowPath->setSuccessors(continuation);
2578
2579 Value* phi = continuation->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Int32, Origin());
2580 successUpsilon->setPhi(phi);
2581 slowPathUpsilon->setPhi(phi);
2582 continuation->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), phi);
2583
2584 auto code = compileProc(proc);
2585 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 0), 31);
2586 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 1), 32);
2587 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 41), 72);
2588 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 42), 73);
2589 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, 43), 666);
2590 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int>(*code, -1), 666);
2591}

2653 proc, trapping(Load), Int32, Origin(),
2654 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &x));

2670 trapsCount++;
2671 }
2672 }

2781void testMoveConstants()
2782{
2783 auto check = [] (Procedure& proc) {
2784 proc.resetReachability();
2785
2786 if (shouldBeVerbose()) {
2787 dataLog("IR before:\n");
2788 dataLog(proc);
2789 }
2790
2791 moveConstants(proc);
2792
2793 if (shouldBeVerbose()) {
2794 dataLog("IR after:\n");
2795 dataLog(proc);
2796 }
2797
2798 UseCounts useCounts(proc);
2799 unsigned count = 0;
2800 for (Value* value : proc.values()) {
2801 if (useCounts.numUses(value) && value->hasInt64())
2802 count++;
2803 }
2804
2805 if (count == 1)
2806 return;
2807
2808 crashLock.lock();
2809 dataLog("Fail in testMoveConstants: got more than one Const64:\n");
2810 dataLog(proc);
2811 CRASH();
2812 };
2813
2814 {
2815 Procedure proc;
2816 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2817 Value* a = root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
2818 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(),
2819 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 0x123412341234));
2820 Value* b = root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
2821 proc, Load, pointerType(), Origin(),
2822 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 0x123412341334));
2823 root->appendNew<CCallValue>(proc, Void, Origin(), a, b);
2824 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin());
2825 check(proc);
2826 }
2827
2828 {
2829 Procedure proc;
2830 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
2831 Value* x = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
2832 Value* a = root->appendNew<Value>(
2833 proc, Add, Origin(), x, root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 0x123412341234));
2834 Value* b = root->appendNew<Value>(
2835 proc, Add, Origin(), x, root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), -0x123412341234));
2836 root->appendNew<CCallValue>(proc, Void, Origin(), a, b);
2837 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin());
2838 check(proc);
2839 }
2840}
